n\n3. **Settings Provider (pkg/setting/provider.go)**\n   - `OSSImpl.Current()` returns a `SettingsBag` (map[string]map[string]string) of all current settings\n   - Each value is passed through `RedactedValue()` with the full environment key name\n   - `OSSImpl.CurrentVerbose()` returns settings with source information (DB vs System)\n   - The provider enforces fine-grained access control via RBAC scopes: `settings:*`, `settings:SECTION:*`, `settings:SECTION:KEY`\n\n## Configuration Flow Summary\n\nThe configuration loading flow in `pkg/setting/setting.go:Load()` → `loadConfiguration()` is:\n1. Load defaults.ini\n2. Apply command-line default properties (cfg:default.*)\n3. Load and merge custom.ini\n4. Apply environment variable overrides (GF_* format)\n5. Apply command-line overrides (cfg:*)\n6. Expand variables in all values ($VAR, ${VAR}, $__file{path})\n7. Initialize logging and data paths\n8. Parse sections via specialized setting_*.go files\n\nWhen the `/api/admin/settings` endpoint is called, the current configuration is retrieved via `pkg/setting/provider.go:OSSImpl.Current()` which applies redaction before returning to the client, ensuring sensitive values like passwords, API tokens, and encryption keys are never exposed in the API response."
